    <string name="triage_result_recommendation_title">(WMT) Recommendation</string>
    <string name="triage_result_recommendation_body">(WMT) Monitor your symptoms and rest. If your condition gets worse, seek medical help.</string>
    <string name="triage_result_category_a_recommendation">(WMT) Patients should immediately be seen by the on call doctor or other medical professional on duty.</string>
    <string name="triage_result_category_b_recommendation">(WMT) Patients should be directed to the emergency department of their nearest hospital.</string>
    <string name="triage_result_category_c_recommendation">(WMT) Patients or patients with worsening symptoms should be referred to the practice nurse or on call doctor.</string>
    <string name="triage_result_category_d_recommendation">(WMT) Patients should be advised to attend the clinic immediately and triaged by the practice nurse (may then be slotted in between appointments or at the end of the session).</string>
    <string name="triage_result_category_e_recommendation">(WMT) Patients should make an appointment for the day and be advised to call back if symptoms worsen.</string>
    <string name="triage_result_category_f_recommendation">(WMT) Patients should make an appointment within 24 hours and call back if symptoms worsen.</string>
